Installation procedure with terminal commands
1.Copy the r.surf.lrm folder to your grass source's scripts folder. Example:
cp -r r.surf.lrm/ ~/source/grass_trunk/scripts/

2. change directory to the r.surf.lrm folder and run make.
cd ~/source/grass_trunk/scripts/r.surf.lrm
make

3. Change directory back to the grass source root directory and run sudo make install. This will update the grass7 install to include the new script. It isn't necessary to re-run configure or make here.
cd ~/source/grass_trunk
sudo make install

